Police have confirmed an argument over the video game system Xbox - seen here in a stock image - lead to the murder of Raymond Galloway

Galloway was rushed to Northwestern Memorial Hospital.

He was pronounced dead about 90 minutes later.

According to a police report, the pair had been fighting earlier in the night while playing Xbox.

Police said the 13-year-old confessed to the crime during an interview with his present.

He was charged as a juvenile with first-degree murder just after midnight on Monday.

Scene: The incident occurred about 5.50am Sunday in this block in Chicago's South Side Bronzeville

It’s not clear where the boy got the gun and no adults have been charged.

Galloway lived in the 4300 block of South Champlain Avenue, a spokeswoman for the Cook County medical examiner’s office said.

